sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Ingress as KServe Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Server as autogluonserver<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant AG as AutoGluon<br/>(in-process)
    participant Cloud as Cloud Storage<br/>S3/GCS/Azure/HF<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Vol as /mnt/models<br/>(Local Volume)

    Note over Client,Vol: Flow 1: Model Loading (Pod Startup)

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Cloud->>Vol: Storage Initializer downloads<br/>model artifacts (HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+)
        Note over Vol: Model saved to /mnt/models
        Server->>Vol: AutoGluonDetectedModel.load()
        Note over Server: Try TimeSeriesPredictor first<br/>then TabularPredictor
        Vol-->>Server: Model artifacts loaded
        Server->>AG: Initialize predictor
        AG-->>Server: Model ready
    end

    Note over Client,Vol: Flow 2: Tabular Inference (v1)

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Client->>Ingress: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kube-rbac-proxy
        Ingress->>Server: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8080 (pod network, no TLS)
        Server->>AG: TabularPredictor.predict(DataFrame)<br/>or predict_proba if PREDICT_PROBA=true
        AG-->>Server: Predictions array
        Server-->>Ingress: JSON response<br/>{"predictions": [...]}
        Ingress-->>Client: HTTPS response
    end

    Note over Client,Vol: Flow 2b: Tabular Inference (v2 Tensor)

    rect rgb(255, 255, 240)
        Client->>Ingress: POST /v2/models/{name}/infer<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kube-rbac-proxy
        Ingress->>Server: Forward InferRequest<br/>HTTP/8080 (pod network, no TLS)
        Server->>AG: Map tensors → DataFrame columns<br/>TabularPredictor.predict()
        AG-->>Server: Predictions
        Server-->>Ingress: InferResponse with typed tensors<br/>(INT64/FP64/BYTES)
        Ingress-->>Client: HTTPS response
    end

    Note over Client,Vol: Flow 3: Time Series Inference (v1 only)

    rect rgb(255, 240, 245)
        Client->>Ingress: POST /v1/models/{name}:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kube-rbac-proxy
        Ingress->>Server: Forward request<br/>HTTP/8080 (pod network, no TLS)
        Note over Server: v2 InferRequest rejected<br/>for time series models
        Server->>AG: TimeSeriesPredictor.predict()<br/>with optional known_covariates
        AG-->>Server: Forecast DataFrame
        Server-->>Ingress: JSON response<br/>{"predictions": [...]}
        Ingress-->>Client: HTTPS response
    end

    Note over Client,Vol: Metrics Scraping

    rect rgb(245, 245, 245)
        participant Prom as Prometheus
        Prom->>Server: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 (cluster-internal)
        Server-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics<br/>(latency, request counts)
    end
